<Action id="38505" issue="26739" author="c0rwin" type="comment" created="2018-01-12 16:21:22.0" updateauthor="c0rwin" updated="2018-01-12 16:21:22.0"> <body><! CDATA {{FilteredBlock}} contains {{FilteredTransaction}} which now looks as following:  {code} //FilteredTransaction is a minimal set of information about a transaction //within a block. message FilteredTransaction { string txid = 1; TxValidationCode tx_validation_code = 2; repeated FilteredAction filtered_action = 3; } {code}  my suggestion is to refactor it down to something like:  {code} //FilteredTransaction is a minimal set of information about a transaction //within a block. message FilteredTransaction { string txid = 1; common.HeaderType type = 2; TxValidationCode tx_validation_code = 3; repeated bytes data = 4; } {code}  where data will be slice of bytes serialized based on the {{common.HeaderType type = 2}} value.  ></body> </Action>
<Action id="38516" issue="26739" author="rickr" type="comment" created="2018-01-12 18:04:26.0" updateauthor="rickr" updated="2018-01-12 18:21:06.0"> <body><! CDATA IMO  message FilteredEnvelope \{ common.HeaderType type = 1; repeated bytes data = 2; // which are now just serialized FilteredTransaction  }  message FilteredTransaction \{ string txid = 1; TxValidationCode tx_validation_code = 2; repeated FilteredAction filtered_action = 3; }  message FilteredBlock \{     string channel_id = 1;     uint64 number = 2; // The position in the blockchain     repeated FilteredEnvelope filtered_envelope = 3; }  ></body> </Action>
